27/07/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The United States has joined Belgrade's efforts to locate and arrest former Bosnian Serb commander Ratko Mladic, said US Ambassador to Belgrade Michael Polt on Monday (26 July). 
His statement came amid reports that the Serbian government is trying to negotiate Mladic's surrender in exchange for financial aid to his family. 
The local media is also reporting that the United States and the EU have called on Belgrade to apprehend him in 20 days or face sanctions. 
(B92, Beta - 27/07/04)
